The paper deals with security and privacy problems and proposes a novel collective classification framework for graph-based analytics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and learning, which are common topics in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of graphs and collective classification further suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for addressing a long-standing challenge, which indicates that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
